headline: Boeing's July aircraft deliveries tumble 20% from June, trailing Airbus
summary: SEATTLE (Reuters) -U.S. planemaker Boeing said on Tuesday that it delivered 48 airplanes in July, down from 60 in June but five more than a year earlier.  Boeing continued to fall further behind European rival Airbus in deliveries this year.  Airbus handed over 67 jets in July despite having a growing number of aircraft unable to be delivered because it lacks enough engines.
